        <num>CC 3081</num>
        <heading>3081.  Effect on novation</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3081.  Effect on novation
A compromise does not effect a novation of the antecedent obligation.  When a party fails to perform a compromise, the other party may act either to enforce the compromise or to dissolve it and enforce his original claim.</p>
        </content>
